edu.ncsu.csc216.carrental.util

Interface SimpleStack<E>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Stack

    public interface SimpleStack<E>
    A simple Stack interface representing a last-in-first-out (LIFO) stack of objects. The usual push and pop operations are provided, as well as a method to peek at the top item on the stack, and a method to test for whether the stack is empty. When a stack is first created, it contains no items.
    Author:
    David Wright
